 :tx/rationale "THE Y-COMBINATOR FOR LLMS. Braid IS the fixed-point combinator that gives stateless LLMs self-reference. The Y-combinator takes a function that can't recurse and gives it recursion via fixed point: f(Y(f)) = Y(f). An LLM is context->continuation with no memory, no self-model, no self-reference. Braid wraps it: seed->session->harvest->store->seed. When this converges, the seed contains exactly the information to produce the session that produces the harvest that produces the seed. Fixed point. Each capability braid adds is Y applied at a different level: Y(memory)=store+seed, Y(self-observation)=daemon, Y(learning)=calibration, Y(inquiry)=FEGH, Y(ontology)=Level 5. The attention mechanism (alpha=E[delta-F(S)]/cost) IS the transformer's attention at knowledge scale instead of token scale. The Hegelian dialectic (thesis/antithesis/synthesis = observation/comparison/reconciliation) IS the harvest/seed cycle IS Y iterating toward fixed point. The GPT was pretrained. Braid makes it post-trained: continuously learning through the same attention mechanism, at organizational knowledge scale."
